	        Send us your pictures   ·  Send us your stories Nairobi - Three Chinese men were arrested over the weekend, with ivory products and lion teeth hidden in condoms, aboard a Kenya Airways flight at the Jomo Kenyatta International Airport. The suspects were traveling from Lubumbashi to Guangzhou, through Nairobi, when Kenya Wildlife Service agents intercepted the illegal goods in the form of bangles and necklaces. According to Capital FM, the source of the goods worth KES 260 000 was yet to be established. The three were expected to appear in court on Monday, NTV said.  24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.  